8:
To think worlds' worth of books 
slumber upon these shelves!
11:
Why, I could sit here reading all day 
and should hardly hope to make a 
dent!
15:
Ahaha, you two really are on the same
wavelength.
18:
You and Claw, I mean. He's an avid 
reader too, isn't he?
21:
Yes, I suppose we DO have more in 
common than you'd expect.
23:
Did he ever tell you how the two of us 
met?
30:
The dogfolk's castle town is better 
equipped for scholarly pursuits than 
his village. So, he snuck in to study.
35:
He WHAT?! Weren't you in the middle 
of a war?!
39:
That's never stopped him. At the time, 
I only saw him as an intruder. Even 
brandished my blade at him!â€”and 
what do you think he did?
41:
Nothing. Absolutely nothing at all. 
I'd venture to say he hadn't even 
noticed the sword at his neck what 
for the book at his nose.
44:
What happened next? Was everything 
all right?
47:
I sheathed my blade, and let him go. 
The adults were none the wiser.
53: You said you didn't know him yet.
57:
Well, for one, we were both children at 
the time.
60:
For another, I'd always been told 
catfolk were uneducated savages. 
And yet, there he was, smarter than 
anyone I'd met before.
63:
It sparked a rivalry between us. 
Somewhere amidst the academic 
debates and one-upping each other, 
we realized our ideals aligned.
67:
Wow... 
So that's why you two decided to push
for peace.
71:
Yes, but we could never have 
managed it alone. I cannot begin to 
express my gratitude to Nimbus.
74:
C'mon, I hardly did anythin'. Just 
stood around while you guys did all 
the talking.
77:
All you needed was a white tiger to 
look the part, right? You could've 
grabbed a random tiger and dunked 
him in flour or something.
83:
I dunno, maybe, but I wouldn't put it 
past Claw.
89:
Preposterous! You sell yourself too 
short, Nimbus. What you 
accomplished was no small feat.
95:
Anyways, what are you doin' here? 
Don't you have your paws full back at 
the castle?
97:
That grouchy old king of yours seemed 
like he'll keep buttin' heads with you 'till 
he kicks it.
100:
If anything, that's precisely why I'd 
best maintain a healthy distance.
103:
Small though it may be, my family 
holds some claim to the throne. 
A fair number of dogfolk wish to see 
me crowned, unfortunately.
107:
Unfortunately?
...You don't want to be king?
111:
I do not. The era of kings will pass. 
Who better to convince people of 
the crown's obsolescence than the 
nasty old codger wearing it?
115:
Reverse psychology, huh? Sounds like 
something Claw would come up with.
124:
So that is where we stand. Would you 
mind if I visited Starview Village from 
time to time?
135: We're happy to have you, Albert.
139:
You don't have to ask. C'mon over 
whenever you want.
146:
I suppose I'll stay here and read for a 
spell.
...I've got work to do if I want to keep 
up with a certain feline friend of mine.
